        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "b436b4582a11163ea86afe97ad935a376a3dabff",
            "subject": "LU-1842 quota: add quota locks support on QMT"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Johann Lombardi",
          "email": "johann.lombardi@intel.com",
          "date": "2012-10-04 08:34:09.000000000",
          "tz": 120
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Johann Lombardi",
          "email": "johann.lombardi@intel.com",
          "date": "2012-10-05 13:11:40.000000000",
          "tz": 120
        },
        "subject": "LU-1842 quota: add acq/rel logic on QMT",
        "message": "LU-1842 quota: add acq/rel logic on QMT\n\nThis patch adds the quota acquire/release logic on the QMT.\nThe QMT is in charge of distributing quota space across quota\nslaves. It grants a significant amount of quota space (75%) initially\nand then tries to balance spare quota space among slaves.\nTo do so, it sends glimpse on per-ID lock to notify slaves of qunit\nshrink. qunit is now the maximal amount of available quota space a\nslave can own. As for qtune, this value (typically 1/4 of qunit) is\nused on the quota slave to decide when to release/pre-acquire quota\nspace.\n\nSigned-off-by: Johann Lombardi <johann.lombardi@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I8064ce614955421681ca1da7e2bb774001ca3bea\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
